'The very worst people, it mattered tremendously to them, which doubled our satisfaction in rejecting them, he said. 'People denied would say there must be a mistake. "When do I get my membership card?" There was no recourse.'

The former director said he once imagined a scheme where he would tell members they could vote to reject someone if they paid for the would-be applicant's annual fee, adding that 'certain people' would have had their membership paid for 20 times over had the rule been implemented.

He added that 'anyone who crows about their success or trades on it is quickly brought down', and that 'people who undersold themselves were likelier to be admitted'.

