In Hollywood Reporter article, showrunners, writers and directors, as well as actors such as Amy Adams and Moderns Family's Jesse Tyler Ferguson, praise the club's privacy, its intimate setting, its cosy design and its stunning 360 degree view of Los Angeles.

One thing Kim Kardasian might have enjoyed at the club was a fun recent installation - called The Fear Of Rejection - consisting of a door with strobe lighting, music and laughter coming from behind it, while a girl with a clipboard and a velvet rope stood in front and told anyone who approached: 'I'm sorry, you're not on the list'.

Justin Bieber, Selena Gomez, Bradley Cooper, Cameron Diaz and Robert Pattinson have all been photographed there, while the article reminisces about parties thrown for Madonna and Keira Knightley.

